      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Einstein coined \"spooky action at a distance\" because the instantaneous correlation seemed to imply that information was being communicated faster than the speed of light. He felt this violated the principle of locality, suggesting some hidden mechanism must be responsible for the apparent connection. However, subsequent experiments by Bell and others confirm this correlation is real, but it cannot be used to send conventional messages faster than light.",
      "source": "target",
