      "content": "The current understanding in quantum mechanics suggests that the particles are not \"aware\" in the classical sense; rather, their properties are described by a single, shared quantum state until measurement occurs. Measuring one particle forces the shared state to \"collapse,\" instantly defining the state of both particles simultaneously across any distance. This non-local correlation is inherently quantum mechanical, suggesting nature functions differently at the fundamental level than our everyday experiences imply.",
